<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-08T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-08T16:00:00-05:00" n="262" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/419: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-08T17:00:00-04:00">June 8, 1933—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>41. You are instructed to proceed with negotiations for the revision
                                of the commercial treaty with Cuba in connection with the
                                Administration’s policy of obtaining reciprocal trade agreements
                                with other countries. The treaty will be submitted to the Senate at
                                the next session of Congress. Public announcement that these
                                instructions have been sent you will be made by the Department
                                probably tomorrow.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>